	(text "Tsumikoro TMC2130 Dual Stepper Controller — rev 0.1\n\nMCU: STM32G0B1KBU6 (UFQFPN-32, USB, same as firmware/tsumikoro-ministepper target)\nLogic supply: 3.3V from TPS54061 PSU sub-sheet (sized for ~100mA logic + 2x TMC2130 VCC_IO)\nMotor supply: VPP — from bus V+ (via JBUS1/JBUS2 pin 1) or external JPWR DC jack,\n             Schottky-OR'd so whichever source is highest wins.\nSense resistors: 0.1 ohm 1% 1210 (2x per TMC) -> ~1.6A RMS max with VFS=325mV\nRS-485 bus: USART2 on PA2/PA3 (no SYSCFG remap needed unlike servo's G030)\n\nComponents placed but NOT wired — wiring pending in KiCad editor.\n\nUSB-C: J_USB with R_CC1/R_CC2 (5.1k to GND) for device/sink mode.\nPA11 = USB D-, PA12 = USB D+. No external crystal needed (HSI48 + CRS).\nSW_BOOT (TS-1187A) connects PA14/BOOT0 to +3V3 when pressed — hold\nduring reset to enter system bootloader (USART2 / I2C1 / SPI1 / USB DFU).\nDRV_ENN moved from PA11 to PB2 (pin 17). TMC2_CS moved from PA12 to PA9 (pin 19).\n\nSTM32G0B1KBU6 UFQFPN-32 Pinout (target wiring):\n  1  PB9           Spare              17 PB2           DRV_ENN (shared)\n  2  PC14          Spare (LSE)        18 PA8           STEP1 (TIM1_CH1)\n  3  PC15          Spare (LSE)        19 PA9           TMC2 CS\n  4  VDD/VDDA      +3V3               20 PC6           DIR2\n  5  VSS/VSSA      GND                21 PA10          Spare\n  6  PF2/NRST      Reset (100nF)      22 PA11          USB D-\n  7  PA0           STEP2 (TIM2_CH1)   23 PA12          USB D+\n  8  PA1           RS-485 DE          24 PA13          SWDIO\n  9  PA2           USART2 TX          25 PA14/BOOT0    SWCLK + BOOT\n 10  PA3           USART2 RX          26 PA15          DIR1\n 11  PA4           TMC1 CS            27 PB3           Limit 2\n 12  PA5           SPI1 SCK           28 PB4           DIAG2\n 13  PA6           SPI1 MISO          29 PB5           Status LED\n 14  PA7           SPI1 MOSI          30 PB6           I2C1 SCL\n 15  PB0           Limit 1            31 PB7           I2C1 SDA\n 16  PB1           DIAG1              32 PB8           Spare\n EP  VSS           GND                -- --            --"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
